,Recommended,221640,8522378,"Posted: 2 January, 2014",all,Ne.Bo.,Still better than Call of Duty
,Recommended,221640,8543194,"Posted: 3 January, 2014",all,Kanaris,"TL;DR- Super Hexagon is amazing and well worth the $3. Heck I would even buy it for $10. Just be prepared to cry a little, and don't buy it if you get nauseous looking at flashy things or are prone to seizures.This game..Wow.Where should I start? At this point I've only had about 5 hours of playing it, but they have been some of the most frenzied and enjoyable hours of my life. I've got to say I've never seen a game like this, and I probably won't again for a long time.In Super Hexagon, you control a triangle which orbits around a hexagon, centered on the screen. Around you, there are light and dark sections, made up of the space between vectors. Within those sections are walls of an outstanding color that come racing toward the Hexagon. You're essentially within a maze of color. If you get hit by a wall, it's game over and your score is submitted automatically so that friends can compete. It may seem like you're trapped, but there is always a way out, no matter how small the gap or how crazy the maneuver you're required to pull. Meanwhile, you have a bunch of crazy lights and effects bouncing around distracting you from the real goal, yet still managing to make the game so much better. On top of this, the music is classic, and superb.Super Hexagon will provide you with 6 different levels, ranging from Hexagon -> Hyper Hexagonest, and from Hard -> Hardes♥♥♥♥♥♥♥. You initially start with the first three- Hard, Harder, Hardest- but once you last for 60 seconds or longer on any of them, the levels go into hyper mode, and you also unlock their hyper mode forms in level select, where you can begin from the 60 second mark at 0 seconds.The way the levels work is that each level has a set of 5-10 'gauntlets' or patterns that it cycles through randomly. So for example, Hexagon will start as a few stray blocks, then it might run its 3x 180 Degree pattern, then its Double Zig-Zag pattern, and then the hexagon in the center will... You'll see ;) . Each level has different patterns, though some are shared throughout the game. Hyper modes contain advanced versions of the patterns used in previous 'normal' levels.Possibly one of the best things about this game is that it only requires two buttons to play. These are Left and Right Arrow, or Buttons 1 and 2 on your mouse. You can also connect a joypad if that's the way you roll. The fact that there is only one speed for the triangle (fast) makes things difficult. After a while you will adjust though, and learn to love the way the game works.Another great feature of Super Hexagon is the fact that once you 'die' from hitting a wall, you can start over within one second, so even if you do somehow manage to rage within this beautiful setting, it probably won't last long, because you'll be off with another try. Other than this, there is an annoying voice when you lose that tells you it's 'gameover' and also one that says 'again' when you retry, but these can be disabled by accessing the game's files and moving the sound files.On top of these things, this game can be booted up and you can be playing any level within 3 seconds. It loads SO FAST.Now, do you think this game is worth it? Would you spend $3 (less than the price of a Big Mac) on this game? I think that you shoul go out and spend your three damn dollars on this amazing game!90/100.ENJOY ^_^"
