,Recommended,221640,25687123,"Posted: 25 September, 2016",all,GROVE4LIFE,"Super Hexagon is an indie video game developed by Terry Cavanagh and released on November 27th, 2012, for PC.It's a simple twitch game in which player is given control of a small triangle, which circles around a figure (hexagon, pentagon or square), and needs to avoid the incoming obstacles in order to survive.Pros:• Simple, yet challenging gameplay;• High replay value;• Highly addictive;• Wonderful, memorable soundtrack;• Global and friends-only leaderboards;• Unforgettable emotions after completing the Hyper Hexagonest stage;• Low price;Cons:• Only 6 different levels;• No widescreen support;In fact, this game is an excellent example of how a good indie game should look like. The idea is not only very original, but is also perfectly brought to life, and the soundtrack fits the game splendidly. All in all, Super Hexagon is totally worth the money, and the emotions upon completion are totally worth the effort.Overall rating: 9/10."
76561198112059304,Recommended,221640,12270915,"Posted: 27 September, 2014",all,Pannacone,"Super Hexagon is more of a virus than a game. Its ludicrously low price during Steam sales makes it a quick fifty cent game for avid users to send to friends (and foes) as a seemingly harmless gift. Most people who receive Super Hexagon even believe it's some sort of joke—after all, it's hard to take such a cheap game seriously at first. But on top of being ridiculously contagious, Super Hexagon tends to leave users in a stunned, almost feverish haze of incredulity. This minimalistic, no-frills action game uses hypnotic trance music and fast-paced action to present players with a heart-palpitating test of mindless reflexes and quick thinking that will keep you coming back to it over and over again.You play Super Hexagon as one of the simplest characters known to gamers: a triangle. Your triangle acts as a little arrow that circles around the center figure of a hexagon. The goal of Super Hexagon is to stop this arrow from being hit by shapes that come into the center hexagon at a speed that ranges from hectically fast to cataclismically hypersonic. The gameplay is incredibly simplistic, but skill-intensive. The levels are short: it takes only sixty seconds to beat each one, though those sixty seconds must be done without any errors. Completing a level can take hours of retries, each one pitting the player against their best time so far.Besides its desperately addictive gameplay, one Super Hexagon's most attractive features is, surprisingly enough, the atmosphere of this psychedelically simple action game. Super Hexagon's arena is something like a dance floor: a rhythmically pulsing, spinning, and twisting battleground set to delectably fast-paced trance music from the artist known as Chipzel. Combined with the outlandishly colorful, outstandingly mesmerizing patterns and shapes that make up Super Hexagon's swirling vortex of ""GAME OVER. BEGIN."", this music forces an attractively frenzied pace on the player.Without a doubt, Super Hexagon is worth the $3 price tag, even though most people purchase it when it's less than a dollar. This game will vex and annoy you to the point of fury, but Super Hexagon's irrationally cutthroat gameplay will always keep you coming back for more punishment. Super Hexagon gains an absurdly strong commendation from me—and the players who manage to complete Super Hexagon with all of the achievements unlocked earn an even more precious look of dazed stupidity and awe on my face."
