,Recommended,221640,8873083,"Posted: 27 January, 2014",all,BEP,"You may have or may not figured from the screenshots but : this is a game where you control a little triangle and dodge whatever is closing in to you , coming from the margins to the centre.This game has 6 levels (hence hexa) , each being beaten after you survive 60 seconds (hence hexa) , maybe this sounds easy , or if not easy , at least a game which does not last long , well the acual gameplay when you win is 6 minutes , but you will be failing so much in the meantime , wich can drive you crazy , but it still gives you an ache to play it more , rather than just making you ragequit. But it is true you will ragequit sometimes , it's unavoidable.There is a lady announcer that tells you your current level when you reach it , the level being just a reference to the time in one level (0 seconds=point 10 seconds=line 20 seconds=triangle 30 seconds=square 45 seconds=pentagon 60 seconds=hexagon).She also tells you 'Begin' at the start and 'Game Over' when you fail to avoid the obstacles , (wich trust me , you will hear a lot) and 'Excelent' when you beat your record , you will be happy when you hear this , but most of the times you will die shortly after.Controls are left and right arrow keys , A and D , left and right mouse buttons , and gamepad.The soundtrack is amazying , in my opinion , and it fits the game realy well.The visuals are like you see in the screenshots , also the game is a little bit flashy and fast , and may give some problems to epileptics.I could detail more , but do you realy need so much reason to buy a 3 euro game that will surely entertain you (but how much is based on your motivation) , and if you have doubts get it at a sale , definately worth it :)"
