,Recommended,221640,23440423,"Posted: 7 June, 2016",all,OregoX,"Super HexagonIt is one of the first in it's genre and also the best.GamePlay:The control of this game just needs to press 2 Buttons. ←,→ or LeftMouse, RightMouse;The Game is very simple, yet challenging.. The name already tells us that this game has to do with hexagons and yes. You're playing a triangle which moves in circles around a hexagon, trying to avoid the bar comming from outside to the middle. The first Level is a bit special, because the hexagon turns into a Square and back.Anyway, I suppose more than 4 points isn't possible. :/★ ★ ★ ★ ☆Graphics:hmmmm... Simple... and perhaps you feel like the 3rd Level is on LSD.^^ But all in one this graphic fits to the game.★ ★ ★ ★ ☆Leveldesign:As I've already mentioned it, e.g. the first Level has the Square-Special-Thing, many Levels have different stuff to offer. The 3rd Level has a quick 180° turn, which is quite confusing if you're not common with that.^^Something which is impossible to avoid, is to memories some patterns of certain level. Which pattern appears is random, but they look always the same and of course it's a useful skill to win. :)After you've got 60 sec. on a level the level changes from: Lvl1 -> Lvl4, Lvl2 -> Lvl5, Lvl3 -> Lvl6,Lvl4 -> Lvl4(Special), Lvl5 -> Lvl5(Special), Lvl6 -> Lvl6(Special) [Note: A Special Level is the part after 60 sec of a certain Level beyond 3!]After 120 sec. the Level changes again and so on.(e.g. If you start at Lvl1 -> Lvl4 -> Lvl4(Special) -> Lvl5 -> Lvl5(Special) -> Lvl6 -> Lvl6(Special)So you see they prevent an repetition by changing the levels.★ ★ ★ ★ ★Music:Music:First the music was not my taste. After playing longer and longer, it get better and better. So at the end I really liked the music.^^ A bit weird, isn't it?The Game contains 3 ½ Soundtrack. Each Lvl pair 1-4,2-5,3-6 have one and the ending song which is actually a reversed version of the last one. That's why I wrote ½. :pbtw: After you finish the 6th Level (get 60 sec.) you've beaten the game and when you die, a kind of credits appear. The game plays the music of the last Level reversed and the bars now came out of the hexagon. It was an amazing feeling and of course a awesome ending.★ ★ ★ ★ ☆At the end, i think it's worth to buy Super Hexagon. Makes fun. Cheap. Challenging.Sadly just 4/5 Points... :/★ ★ ★ ★ ☆"
