,Recommended,221640,27106898,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,Lord Anthropophaginian,"You begin the game as a lone, perfect triangle, the last of your kind. You soon discover that you're not the only being in this universe as you are quickly rushed by hoards of irregular shapes, jealous of your perfection. You have been granted with powers of lateral movement, which you can use to inverse-circle strafe. You have no weapons - Fortunately, these irregular shaped beings are not too bright; with a well timed side-step, they'll rush themselves into the void and be obliterated.This might seem very straightforward, but the universe itself plots against you - warping and spinning the landscape to disorientate the player.You are not completely alone, however, as a narrator/companion helps you on your way. When you reach certain goals, she grants you various morale boosts. She will let you know when you've achieved your goal, but also gently lets you down when you fail. If you're up for a challenge - you can play for 120s through and unlock the secret dialogue with her.Upon completion of the game, the universe concedes defeat and no longer pulls its landscape-changing stunts. However, the hoards are ever present, allowing you to play on after finishing the main quest.Features:*Six unique universes*Impeccable naration*Outstanding soundtrack*Lots of nice coloursScore: Δ/Δ"
