,Recommended,221640,11491179,"Posted: 31 July, 2014",all,水,"Holy crap, this game is addictive... for such simple controls, mastering them is no easy task at all. Left moves you left around the hexagon, right moves you right, and you must avoid the oncoming obstacles. Sounds simple, right? Ha, I've only just begun to learn how difficult it can get (I've just unlocked Hyper Hexagonest mode) and certain patterns can be seen, but learning to cope with those, that's the real challenge. In terms of soundtrack, this game has Chipzel on the board, and even after resetting the game probably a million times, the music never drove me insane, it's that good. I can happily listen to Focus and Otis on repeat for many many hours on end. Courtesy is still good, but it's a bit more toned down, which suits the stage, but it's not as good for random listening, in my opinion, as Otis or Focus.Overall, this game gets a 9.5/10 from me. It lost 0.5 because sometimes the controls can wander off on their own sometimes, even just breifly, but that could be a problem on my end."
