,Recommended,221640,8673937,"Posted: 11 January, 2014",all,zerokeu,"Imagine a technicolor honeycomb trying to eat a tortilla chip. But it's going about doing so in the most flashy way possible. And that little triangular chip is you, the player.That's kind of what Super Hexagon looks and feels like. Kind of.Super Hexagon is a game that is very well-designed, both visually, mechanically, and stylistically. This game is very straightforward both in concept and execution, which allows it to have solid, refined gameplay. It also has a great soundtrack and progression in difficulty, and a pretty clever ending scene makes it very satisfying to beat.That said, it's also a game that can be very frustrating. If you feel compelled to complete games, prepare to beat your head against a wall if you aren't very good at arcade-style games like these."
,Recommended,221640,18637153,"Posted: 23 October, 2015",all,Twiggy The Giraffe,"Insanely hard...but also insanely good.  This is the type of game you can play for 30 seconds or 30 minutes.  If the tight controls and vibrant colors don't make you want to buy this game (and come on, you should, it's VERY cheap), then the incredible chiptune/electronica soundtrack most definitely will.  And if you thought the first stage was impossible, then guess what?  You're not even close to done.  There's five more hair-pullingly difficult stages after that, but the music...oh, jeez, the music...it's gonna keep you coming back for more, trust me.  Despite the crazy difficulty of this game, I never quit it because of how much of a visual and audible spectacle it was every single time I played it.  And that's what insanely hard games like this need: an addicting hook that keeps you wanting to play no matter how hard it gets.  And when I say this game is hard, I mean that one playthough could last anywhere from one second to thirty, depending on how good your reflexes are.  It's THAT hard...and that's only the first stage.  But if you're like me, you won't play this for the difficulty.  You'll play it for the vibrant lights and killer sound.  Pick this up.  Now."
