,Recommended,221640,17811761,"Posted: 31 August, 2015",all,Blaziken,"If you get this game, please don't think 'this is too hard' and never play it again. If you put even just an hour into it you will see yourself improving massively.The music is great and fits incredibly well, the game is addictive and immersive, and beating each level is increasingly more challenging but insanely more rewarding. Finally getting to that 60 seconds mark is so fulfilling, especially after thinking how hard it was when you first loaded the game. Beating the last stage is possibly the most rewarding and satisfying thing I have ever experienced in gaming, no exaggeration.One piece of advice - every so often, go onto a harder level for 5 minutes or so. When you go back to the easier one you were trying previously, it will feel incredibly slow and make it much easier, at least for the first few levels."
76561198119897083,Recommended,221640,20455070,"Posted: 10 January, 2016",all,Atlas,"Ok, so while I don't have many hours on the steam version of this game, I have SEVERAL into the iOS version.  I have beaten the game, 2 minutes per level, and figured I'd write a review.Pros:- The game is crazy fun.  Seriously.  It can be a pain to get into, but when you end up getting to a number like 56 seconds, it feels impossible to put the game down before completeing said level.- Fair.  Contrary to popular belief (based off of what I've heard), this game is very fair.  However, it is NOT forgiving (see cons).  If you have good reactions (and have played enough to memorize the patterns), the game actually isn't that hard.- It's competitive.  No, I don't mean that in the same way E-Sports is.  I mean, if you have multiple friends who all enjoy this game, it's a decent game to compete for high-scores in.- Soundtrack.  Enough said.Cons:- Repetitive.  This game doesn't ever chage.  That's why once you memorize the patterns, the game get's easy, and quickly.- Flashing lights.  The game can cause headaches if you aren't careful.  If you have epilepsy, stay away.- The skill gap is absurd.  When you first pick this game up, it will feel like HELL.  I remember literally throwing my phone across my room, complaining that it was impossible.  Improving is a struggle.- Unforgiving.  You don't get three lives.  One mistake, you're out, and have to restart.  Granted, you only have to stay alive for 60 seconds, so a death isn't all that destructive in terms of progress.  But still, this is rather tedious, and requires perfection.Overall, I'd highly recommend this game, it's a nice throwback to retro that's highly enjoyable, even if only for a little while ^_^"
