,Recommended,221640,19064432,"Posted: 13 November, 2015",all,Zaphite,"Super Hexagon is a rhythm/music game that requires fast reactions to move out of the way of obstacles that come at you all while being able to enjoy a great soundtrack and psychedelic visuals.The Good:This game is a minimalistic game, but that doesn't at all detract from the addicting gameplay and large amounts of enjoyment to be had. The only controls are left and right which are used to move your cursor around the center of the screen, which is where the obstacles come from, which are basically just lines. This may sound very simple but the game uses the energetic music, vibrant colors, and lots of movement to create a very intense atmosphere that makes you want to keep trying in order to last as long as possible in each level. There is plenty of content for only $2.99, the gameplay stays consistent throughout but later levels add in some different elements to make it harder. The overall difficulty is fairly high, but every time you die you want to start right back up again so I would say that it is well balanced in that respect. As I briefly mentioned earlier, the music in the game is great and without it or even maybe with different music, the game would not be nearly as good.The Bad:The combination of movement and colors could potentially make some people have headaches or feel ill, if you have a tendency to react badly to these types of games then I would recommend taking caution before purchasing the game. Although I believe the difficulty of the game to be fairly well balanced, others may feel that the game is much too difficult and get frustrated easily. Occasionally, the controls can seem a little too ""slippery"" but it didn't stop me too much from playing the game and is not a major problem.For only $2.99, Super Hexagon keeps you on the edge of your seat and makes you want to retry every time you die, with a great combination of movement, visuals, and music that creates a very intense and energetic game."
