,Recommended,221640,8916792,"Posted: 30 January, 2014",all,THE BANE POOOOOOST,"It's one of the most evil games I've played in the last few months, and addictive. It'll make you swear like a sailor for hours while you desperately try to beat your score, even by a fraction of a second; all of this is in the name of 'progression'. It's made worse when you set your sights on that ambitious score your friend got earlier. The music isn't bad either, and it's very retro-chiptune in style. But if you dislike it, you can also choose to mute the music and play your own in the background and rock out to something while you die over and over again.Visually, the game screws with you, horribly. You'll feel completely dazed and confused while you're trying to navigate away from the impending death-blocks flying towards your cursor. It takes several attempts before you get a solid handle on how to move and avoid the blocks. It's a very neat game to break out at a gathering of friends and watch them struggle and curse at it while they try to last beyond 12 seconds.I rate this game highly, and I still have yet to plumb the depths of the harder difficulty settings. I only just recently went beyond a minute at the easiest setting, and I shudder to imagine getting good enough at the game to last as long on the upper echelons. I've even purchased copies for family and friends. Get this game and give it a shot, especially if you're hankering after some good old fashioned classic gaming."
