76561198085057223,Recommended,221640,8723849,"Posted: 15 January, 2014",all,That Guy,"Super Hexagon is, as the store page implies, a minimalist action game. Or, to be more precise, a ""twitch"" reflex game. This game challenges you to, as a triangle orbiting a [spinning, strobing] hexagon, survive for 60 seconds--just one minute--in a minefield of walls headed towards the hexagon your triangle is orbiting. While a lot of people don't have the patience to practice such a seemingly fruitless game enough to get past the first levels (the third, ""Hexagonest"" being my everest for the longest time), once you sink an hour or so in the game and finally survive the first level, it feels, well, about as rewarding as a twitch game can get, which scales precisely on how difficult it was to complete the level and how many tries it took to finally unlock the next one. For just three dollars, this is a really good game, and I'd definitely recommend others buy it... that is, if they can handle the mind-melting strobe effects on top of a rapidly spinning playing field.Warning: if there is ANY chance that rapidly flashing lights could cause any adverse reactions (well, greater than getting annoyed, that is) in you, DO NOT TOUCH THIS GAME."
