,Recommended,221640,9029812,"Posted: 9 February, 2014",all,BananaInspector,"5 - Must have title.A real case study in flawless game design; the most simple of concepts and a ridiculously steep learning curve mean that each second on the clock is a tense and hard fought battle, and your own reaction times are the only thing standing in your way. I remember watching the trailers of this game just before I bought it and thinking, there's no way anyone could do that; it was too fast and disorientating, now I catch myself thinking that same level is ridiculously easy and it totally rocks. Few games give you the same sense of achievement as beating any one of Super Hexagon's levels because each one is so infuriatingly hard. It's basically the Dark Souls of arcade gaming, except the pc version is actually good.Play it with friends, it's cheap enough to get a few copies for the price of a coffee, and you'll spend a lot longer than you anticipated in the maddeningly simple yet utterly impossible hexagon."
