,Recommended,221640,8266578,"Posted: 24 December, 2013",all,DRUNK_CANADIAN,"Super Hexagon. An Indie game, which although to be honest should probably be marketed as a freeware, is worth a purchase if on sale <1$. The game is essentially you rotating a triangle around a hexagon and dodging lines coming toward you while electronic music plays in the background. The pros are that it is a very simple game and is challenging yet still manages to be enjoyable. However it is a game you will likely only play for minutes at a time. The cons are it is simply too difficult and the controls of rotation are often not precise meaning you depressing the key for what you precieve as the appropriate amount of time to do a 180 degree rotation may over or undershoot you, and the game mechanics make this unforgiving (should be a little more generous to human error). At its core the progression through this game is a memory game, and for that is actually quite enjoyable and I'm sure a workout for your brain as you try to keep all the motions in your head to progress further...also you get gane over a lot. Still recommended, but only for a reduced price."
