,Recommended,221640,7870486,"Posted: 1 December, 2013",all,eltee,"Music is great, and actually completing to more advanced levels can be a pretty powerful driving hook.  One thing to be wary of though is going to be the 'input lag' of your monitor/screen.  Its not a metric that comes up often and isn't something alot of display makers spend much time advertising/promoting.  Its basically the amount of time between when your computer sends a frame to the screen, and when the screen actually shows it to you.  The very best/fastest gaming monitors can have it down to 2-3ms, while the very worst/oldest/slowest ones can be 50-60ms or more.In a game like this, where literally every single millisecond against your reflexes counts, having the right or wrong screen can easily make the difference between making it to the next level and crashing and burning hard on a wall you barely had time to register coming.So yeah, super ultra twitch/reflexes based.  Even still though, the music is catchy enough that its worth a look despite what could ultimately be a very frustrating/demotivating slew of 5 second deaths.(7/10) (One alternative for those without ultra fast reflexes would be to just look up the soundtrack out there)"
