,Recommended,221640,32077254,Posted: 30 May,all,<|°_°|>,"TL;DR: Buy this game now, it's like nothing else you'll ever experience when you get in the zone.  When it sucks you in, it feels like there is nothing in the universe except you and Super Hexagon.  It's dirt cheap, so it wouldn't take much to make this game worth your money,  and it goes way above and beyond that standard.  Hard, fast, intense, mind-affecting, satisfying, and addictive - the videogaming meth.In Super Hexagon, you control a tiny arrow, and your sole objective is to dodge increasingly-fast-and-complicated patterns of murderous walls.  Each stage lasts only 60 seconds.  'Survive for one minute?  Easy peasy,' you say.  Not so.  This is probably the hardest game I've ever played, at least as far as sheer difficulty of completion is concerned.This game is crazy difficult, but not in an artificial 'I got you' way, like I Wanna Be the Guy or Dark Souls.  Every time you die, it was *your* fault, and then you mash the spacebar and try again.  And again.  And again.  Sometimes you will be frustrated, you will die 10 seconds in 12 times in a row.  But sometimes... sometimes you get into 'the zone,' that mythical feeling where all other sensations drop out and you become one with the Hexagon.  It's incredible - and I'm not exaggerating here, when you really get absorbed into this game it's like nothing else on planet Earth.  The feeling of finally beating a level you'd been working for ages is incomperable, like a...(Sorry for stealing your joke, Bo Burnham c:)The music is great - intense, upbeat chiptunes - and offers some rhythmic assistance for each level (although maybe that's just me and my musical mind).  There's not much to talk about regarding the graphics - simple, conveys the information it needs to.There's not really anything I would change about this game - 10 hours of gameplay ago I would have asked to please get rid of the fast right-right-left-left-left pattern on the hardes♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ level - but having beaten that stage, I can say that it was I who was the problem, not the game itself.I rate this game 10/10 - meaning that there is nothing I would change about it, it perfectly achieved what it set out to achieve (not necessarily that it is my favorite game of all time, though it's up there)."
