,Not Recommended,221640,8460257,"Posted: 31 December, 2013",all,such aByZMal much bad,"Dear reader/gamerThis game is for people who look for cheap ways of finding addicition, if it grows on them. Personally, I don't even think this is worth the 2 pounds it is priced at. It is just one of those get rich quick schemes by game designers, which we have seen before where suddenly a dumb game is very addictive. It is the most abnormally frustrating and infuriating game I have ever played, and I mean it.Basically you control a stupid little triangle usingthe left and right arrow keys to dodge incoming lines (refer to trailer) at a very fast speed, in tune to a not very calming soundtrack, which you would expect to hear in a rowdy nightclub. It could be of use in testing your reflexes, but it is simply annoying, especially the monotone female voice who repeatedly says ""Game Over"".If you are still undeterred to buy this game, then I am sorry, but you have problems."
76561197993623800,Not Recommended,221640,8601255,"Posted: 6 January, 2014",all,epilardus,"Super Hexagon is the gaming equivalent of modern art. Where you see a blank square hanging on the gallery wall with a dash of red paint, the critics rave about ""the stark presentation contrasting with a bold use of color, challenging the eye and the expectations and slyly satirizing our own feelings of inadequacy."" And so it goes with Super Hexagon. Critics rave about its ""astounding"" minimalism and ""elegance."" That's because they, as sophisticated consumers of media, ""get it,"" and you, Neanderthal that you are, have no taste.Well, as a Neanderthal myself, I found it to be a simplistic and hyperactive waste of time with the production values of an Ed Wood film.On the plus side, the game does bring together some elements of classic gaming: It's got the graphics of Atari's Adventure, the gameplay of Cow Clicker, and the music of a Game Boy game hopped up on meth.Now, I'm not saying that this game isn't for anyone; if you hate the slow, deliberate pacing and deep, complicated story of Wario Ware games, Super Hexagon may be just the game for you.I think I paid 30 cents for it and, at night, those three dimes hover in the air over my bed and torment me with their laughter.There's very little to this game; if this is Super Hexagon, and can only imagine what Hexagon was like."
