76561198002256206,Not Recommended,221640,8566846,"Posted: 4 January, 2014",all,elizabethdemra,"I bought this game because the idea seemed so cool, and not something I'd seen before, and it just looked like simple fun.  (Not 'simple' meaning 'easy' but 'simple' meaning 'not complex'.)However, this is not the game for me AT ALL.  I'm still sure lots of people will find it fun, I'm just warning you that if you're not good with directions / hand-eye coordination / reflexes, then this game is going to be ludicrously frustrating.  In addition, I started getting a headache within about 15 minutes of playing, in part because I was focusing so hard on trying to go the right direction (and failing, and tensing up my shoulders, which caused/worsened the headache, etc.)This is NOT a ""hard-negative"" review (meaning I don't think anyone would enjoy the game), just a ""soft-negative"" to say think about how easily irritated you are, and whether you think focusing on the video full-screen for long periods of time might make your head throb.  If neither of those things concern you, then certainly buy this game and have fun.  It still looks interesting and original, and I really wish I could enjoy it."
