,Recommended,221640,2369558,"Posted: 5 September, 2013",all,8Bit64,"Super Hexagon is a super addicting reflex-destroying monster of a game. You move your triangular player marker through tunnels of receding trapezoids around a hexagon center until you eventually hit a wall. Though the visuals are simple, this is one of the hardest reflex-based games I've ever played. Though the game is amazingly hard, the incredible music that doesn't get on your nerves the literal thousandth time you've heard it and the compelling feeling to play ""just one more round"" keep the game from getting old quickly. If you are to survive a full minute of disorienting, shifting, spinning, flashing and turning, you unlock harder levels for you to try and overcome. This is a wonderful game to play if you've got 5 minutes with nothing to do, or are hoping for a real challenge. The game gets so hard, it's more than likely you will not beat the final level. It's so ludicrously fast,  that unless you are obsessive and/or masochistic, you'll probably never have the patience to beat it. If you're looking for a game that will give your reflexes a serious kick in the♥♥♥♥♥ look no further than Super Hexagon!"
