,Recommended,221640,2027317,"Posted: 28 March, 2013",all,Blazephlozard,"This game is very very very very hard. If you can't beat Cotton Alley Dark World or The Kid's stage in SMB, this isn't for you. If you gave up on the ""Veni Vidi Vici"" trinket in VVVVVV, this isn't for you. Even if you've done those, only the first two stages in this are for ANYONE.I really can't support a game that, I feel, was designed to be practically unbeatable. And I really believe the Hyper stages in this were. In that sense this game is a lot like Kaizo Mario World. Except, without savestates. Yeah. That doesn't sound fun, does it? That being said, the ""Hexagon"" and ""Hexagoner"" levels (the first two of six) are very playable and very fun. The other four though... jeez. Good luck with that.Also, I don't like how flashy the graphics are. The spinning and zooming and panning and twisting and flashing make this already hard game impossible. Too often you can't keep track of yourself. It's just like BIT.TRIP BEAT, except, missing one beat in that doesn't equal game over.Watch gameplay videos of it first, and really think to yourself, ""could I survive in that for more than 30 seconds, ever?"" If you can, I'd say it's worth a dollar or two. The first two levels are worth what I paid for it."
