,Recommended,221640,9157491,"Posted: 17 February, 2014",all,Mona,"This is Super Hexagon. A simple little game that seems like your average rage game. Well my friends, let me tell you. This isn't your average rage game. This is a game that was created by the sick, sadistic mind of gaming's Satan himself, Terry Cavanagh. Now before you start writing death threats to him on his Twitter, or whatever, he isn't a bad person... He just has a sick sense of humor. His previous creation, VVVVVV, is a game, I highly recommend, and if you wanna hear what I have to say about it, just look at my review on it when I actually write it. But anyways, enough rambling. The game starts off with three levels. Hexagon: Hard Mode, Hexagoner: Harder Mode, and Hexagonest: Hardest mode. But there's three other levels to unlock. To unlock these levels, as well as beat the level itself, you have to survive getting hit by parts of a hexagon that twist around, and even change the shape of the hexagon itself ranging to a pentagon, and a square. But that's only in Hexagon. But anyways, you have to guide a little triangle (you) around these obstacles so you don't die. But you have to do this for at least 60 seconds to unlock the hyper level (essencially the hard mode of the level), and beat the level itself. Sounds simple, right? NO. It's simplistic nature throws you into a brick wall when you actually get into the game itself. Now let me be frank. This game is not bad by any means, but if you have a lack of patience, DO. NOT. GET. THIS. GAME. Otherwise, go ahead."
