,Not Recommended,221640,24435133,"Posted: 20 July, 2016",all,TundraTurtle,"Good music and a classic score attack game, but if you like this you already own it.Though there are some glaring issue of design, in my opinion. The system of moving your triangle around the hexagon works well enough but there is no feedback in the movement so the screen backgrounds rapidly accelerating and spinning makes it incredibly difficult to not overshoot or undershoot by just tapping the keys. The spinning of the screen as well is it's own problem as making things difficult to see is not a fun concept of challenge, merely difficulty created by poor design. In my opinion, throwing unrelenting challenges at you and then making them hard to differentiate, then make it purposefully hard to dodge said challenges on your own skill and knowledge of the patterns is not good design.In short, any game where you have every pattern memorized and every movement known just to die because the screen decided to have a trip on a roundabout at 90MPH is not challenging, it's frustrating and not fun to overcome."
