,Not Recommended,221640,22363405,"Posted: 11 April, 2016",all,Fyuchanick,"I had to refund this game. I wanted to like this game, since it is very popular, has good music, and was made by Terry Cavanagh, creator of VVVVVV. However, the gameplay is too minimalistic. You retry the same level over and over, memorizing patterns, and almost nothing changes each time. You know what DOES change every time you die though? Your position. Your position is practically the only thing that doesn't reset when you die. However, if it was moving when you died, it will stay in that position, and will be annoyingly offset. Rarely, it may even make the game unplayable, causing you to become stuck on an angle that make some level configurations literally impossible. And by rarely, I mean in terms of death, not time, so considering the amount of times you will die, it is actually quite common. I probably experienced an instance of that within my first few minutes of playing. Seriously, there are plenty of other games that have insane levels of difficulty, with more satisfaction as well."
