,Not Recommended,221640,25631896,"Posted: 22 September, 2016",all,D YellowMadness,"I like the concept & the difficulty & I beat the first difficulty level in about 40 minutes. What I don't like is that the hardest patterns are so rare & random that you're more likely to win by replaying until those patterns don't come up than you are to win by getting good enough to deal with those patterns. It's like playing Slow Ride in Guitar Hero 3 with a random chance of having to suddenly play random riffs from The Devil Went Down to Georgia.The second worst thing about this game is the difficulty spikes. You'll likely find yourself beating some levels in seconds but getting stuck on other levels for a few dozen minutes or more. A few dozen minutes might not sound bad but it takes a lot of deaths for you to be stuck on a 45 second level for a few dozen minutes.If you're incredibly patient & you don't mind an incredibly irratic & inconsistent difficulty curve, you'll probably like this game but, otherwise, I wouldn't reccomend it."
