,Not Recommended,221640,20205224,"Posted: 1 January, 2016",all,TheGreatestDancer,"I am a fan of challenging games such as Dark Souls and Super Meat Boy and this game is certainly very challenging. The main problem is that its difficulty comes mostly from the slippery controls. A game that demands such precision from the player should have flawless controls. It's just not there. It is way too sensitive. The slightest tap on the keyboard (or gamepad, I tried both) sends the arrow flying.Also the fact that the screen keeps changing colors and rotating doesn't help much. It is a gimmicky distraction to the gameplay. This is ""hard"" in the sense that driving with someone constantly covering your eyes is ""hard"". It's pointless. It feels like the developer wants players to fail as a means to an end. As if he wanted to make a very hard game, even though not a very enjoyable one.So in the end what you have is an exercise in frustration. This game is a prime example of a great idea executed very poorly. A little more care and this could have easily been a classic. I'd suggest anyone looking for a hard game to play Super Meat Boy or even 1001 Spikes."
