,Not Recommended,221640,11385772,"Posted: 23 July, 2014",all,951Jimbo,"Super Hexagon is a good example of why things like Metacritic (88/100) can be so flawed.The game is $2.99, a fair price point, but this game just doesn't offer a lot.  The screen swirls around and you have to use your keyboard to move a small marker around the enclosing bars to survive (see a YouTube video).The game is so simplistic, I cannot recommend it.  There is less to do here than in a 30 year old game like Tetris or Space Invaders.  To give this game 88% as a throwback to days when computing power was measured in double digits Mhz is an insult to people that have actually developed good retro games that offer something modern such as Organ Trail or Fez."
