,Not Recommended,221640,7892103,"Posted: 2 December, 2013",all,Deck of Many Things,"I can not honestly recommend this game to anyone without first warning them about its ""difficulty."" While an interesting and fun game for a short while, after many, many attempts at puzzling out its psuedo-random nature, it is easy to see that most of its difficulty is fake.Now, this isn't ""This game is stupidly hard! It must be fake difficulty!"" claims. The game's challenge is genuinely fake, involving random changing speeds and directions of rotations, (mostly) unpredictable, radical changes in the playing field, and an obscenely small margin of error. Altogether, this makes Super Hexagon more an excercise in tenacity and repitition than a challenging, rewarding puzzler.Avoid the game, unless you enjoy constant interface screws and ball-busting unforgivability hidden under excellent music and a simplistic, but charming, interface."
