76561198082000407,Not Recommended,221640,15807785,"Posted: 12 May, 2015",all,Terry,"WARNING: Do not play this game, it is thinly veiled Devil worship.What first attracted me to this game, I can't remember, and after seeing it for what it really is, I dare not look back to find out.The game consists of a single screen in which you play a triangle connected to a hexagon. Your goal as the triangle is to avoid the incoming shapes as they approach the hexagon and are absorbed into it. If they touch you, the game ends. While this may seem an innocent setup, the hexagon's six sides, six stages within each game mode, and six game modes within the game are anything but an innocent coincidence. In reality, the player as the triangle is caught in a nightmare realm, where the Devil, whose mouth is the hexagon, feeds on the lesser shapes and lines that approach It, which the player must avoid for as long as they can, for if the player is hit by one, they are pushed by it right into the six-sided mouth of the Devil.Like Tetris, this game is unwinnable and only allows you to hold off your inevitable defeat, implying that the Devil is an all-powerful figure who will inevitably ""eat"" us all. This is not truthful by any stretch of the imagination, but unfortunately those who do not see the game for what it is may gradually come to believe it.The only redeeming aspect of this game is its music, and even that is purposed to lure the untrained mind into a trance so that it remains blind to the evil scheme in front of it. Please avoid this game at all costs and spread the word in your youth groups so nobody else falls victim to this manifestation of the Devil's handiwork."
