,Recommended,221640,10234671,"Posted: 25 May, 2014",all,updownbanana,"Super Hexagon is a great game. You are a triangle that circles around a hexagon in the center of the screen. Various obstacles converge towards the center of the hexagon, and you have to dodge them. Also, the screen spins around while you play. There are 6 difficulty levels; you start out with the first three, Hexagon, Hexagoner, and Hexagonest, then you unlock the hyper version of each difficulty level once you've survived for a minute in that difficulty. It sounds very simple, but it's actually extremely hard. Most people can only last 3 seconds starting out. This doesn't deter most people, though; as you play, you'll start to recognize patterns and work out how to dodge everything. It can keep you playing for a long time, due to multiple difficulty levels and constantly trying to beat your high score. I think it's definitely worth the price.tl;dr: This game is very difficult, but very fun and worth your 3 dollars."
