,Recommended,221640,8420587,"Posted: 29 December, 2013",all,MalkDuds,"For such a simple game, Super Hexagon has incredible replayability.  The concept is simple: make your character (a triangle) dodge the incoming lines.  These walls are coming to the center of the screen from the outside, and all you have to do is dodge left or right.Easier said than done.  Hop right into the easiest difficulty, which is Hard (also named Hexagon).  Each mode has a hyper mode that is unlocked when you survive for 60 seconds.  Good luck getting there on Hexagonest.The challenge of this game is very simple, and thus can be very relaxing, if you just sit back, let loose, and don't take it seriously.  Test your perception, reaction time and reflexes, and sensitivity as each mode increases the speed your triangle moves as well as how fast the lines come in at you.This game can be incredibly fun if you like challenges.  The challenge of it is somewhat like the bullet hell shooters, but more satisfying and less overwhelming.  Definitely much easier with a controller, though."
