,Recommended,221640,774492,"Posted: 2 April, 2013",all,Ultralord,"This game is just plain old hard. It provides an extreme challenge, while keeping the actuall graphics simple. Let me start off by explaining the game. You, a subject of an over extreme mind experiment, are part of a line to g oin the arena. In the arena you must swerve your way around your enemys, who are quiet dumb if I may say so. Most don't make it through the first 3 seconds of a round start, literally. Now can you prove to beat this huge challenge and bring home the Hexagons? Now that that's out of the way, lets get to the gameplay. The distractions, there are so many distractions. The screen spins, there a multible colors to confuse you, and the speed of the triangle is awkward. This creates a thrilling, action packed, quick atmosphere. The graphics, are not that hard to recreate. Simple shapes that are polished to fit the theme, and the simplicity help the game. Overall, this game is simple, proves a challenge, and is actually rewarding after you beat the first 10 seconds, it's a great game. I can't find anything wrong about it besides the players that play it. 9.5/10 Since I cant be sure if this game is not without the few bugs."
