,Recommended,221640,10743576,"Posted: 23 June, 2014",all,USER 5,"Super. Hexagon.I really like this game, and I'm not sure why. Everything it does should make me hate it, but I just straight up enjoy it. Maybe it's the music. Maybe it's the knowledge that I am in fact getting better at it (as reflected by my best time), or maybe it's that everyone thinks I'm some kind of god when I can survive for more than ten seconds on the hardest level (hardes♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ I think).The music is amasing, and is what I found myself coming back to this game for. And once you play a  more difficult level, the easier ones are much, much easier. I have spent over 33 hours in this game, because I also own it on android (which is harder than PC for some reason).In case you didn't get it, this game is really hard. You are a tiny triangle that can move around the outside of a hexagon. You either go left, or right. As you do, there are falling 'blocks' that will squish you if they catch you inbetween themselves and the hexagon you are travelling around. These blocks only fall where a side of the hexagon is. Dodging them can be very tricky, but the game is distracting. Watch the trailer if you don't believe me. It spins, it changes colour, it warps and zooms in and out all the time. Try and keep track while you die."
