,Recommended,221640,2114606,"Posted: 24 January, 2013",all,Rox,"Now THIS is a video game. You are a cursor. You move left and right to avoid obstacles. Your time to death, measured in hundredths of a second, is your score. Survive each stage for 60 seconds. It's a deceptively simple concept, but the way it's executed, with pleasant colors pulsing to the chiptune soundtrack and hypnotic shapes seemingly drawing you into the screen as they spin out of control, makes for a very addictive experience. When it looks so easy, and when each play session can be counted in seconds, it's so very hard not to try just one more time."
