,Recommended,221640,21355976,"Posted: 20 February, 2016",all,UltPokenonFan,"Super Hexagon is amazingly simple. You are a small pointer who moves around a hexagon. You have to avoid the deadly, flashy lines coming at you. But it is hard, and discouraging. You must keep trying.The music is amazing. There are tthree really epic chiptune tracks, one for each level. Everytime you start a level a different part of the song plays, to keep you interested.There are only a few cons I can think of. The first is that it's very hard to learn, and will easily discourage many players.Secondly, the sounds in game are very annoying. You are constantly hearing 'begin' and 'game over' everytime you die. Also, every 10 or 15 seconds you get to be told what level of the level you are on; 'line' 'triangle' 'square' 'pentagon' 'hexagon'.And if you turn vsync off to save yourself from input lag, the visuals becomes very choppy, might be better on powerful PCs.Overall it's not bad, but many things could be done better. 8/10.Conflicted about this game?If the sounds are bothering you, go into the game's folder on your hard drive and replace the offending sounds with blank sound files. If you don't like the music, you can replace it (look up guide here on steam).If it's too hard, look up some guides. Super Hexagon 101 is the most useful.If 2.99 is too much for an awesome game, go try Open Hexagon. It's the same concept, just free and open-soure."
