,Recommended,221640,8269092,"Posted: 24 December, 2013",all,Harambae,"I don't usually write a review for a game after only playing it for about an hour, but I gotta say, this game is SO fun. The gameplay is not like any other game I've played. You rotate around whatever the current shape is and try to avoid the oncoming lines. You have to snap back and forth, rotate in time, or zig zag your way around them to progress. While doing this, the game can ♥♥♥♥ with you, but it's in a good way. Colors change and the whole field can warp and rotate itself which adds to the difficulty, and, in my opinion, the fun. Not to mention the amazing music which is sort of techno-ish mixed with 8bit music. All in all a great deal. Especially for the price point."
