,Recommended,221640,8349705,"Posted: 27 December, 2013",all,Thiefy,"I was just like you once... Start up the game, dance in your chair to the sick music, only to have it pause 4.23 seconds later at a game over screen.I'm a bit of a sore loser, but I wasn't sore about losing on this game; just like alot of classic arcade games, this game demands twitch reflexes, acute spatial recognition, and some good ol' muscle memory to progress further. The joy brought by each miniscule progression further into the game and the music; 8.62 seconds, 10.46 seconds... It's like setting a new record on a classic arcade game.Turn on Arcade Mode, where everyone competes to put their name in the list of top times, and Super Hexagon IS a classic arcade game, just envisioned in another age. Nostalgia, anyone? Start this up at a party with a controller, and you'll have people crowding for a try, like back in the day at an arcade, or at the very least bouncing to the beats, like Guitar Hero.The challenge this game provides scratches an itch I haven't been able to get to for quite some time, and with the ridiculously low price tag, the purchase is a no-brainer. Hell, the music alone's worth it."
