,Recommended,221640,14060345,"Posted: 18 January, 2015",all,ESC_Artiste,"Super Hexagon~Super Difficult, Super FunWell...where do I even begin.I had just recently completed this game, gaining extreme bragging rights. Let me say that it is a b**** to play. However, it's a fun b****, I must say.Controls are very simple. Go left and right. That's it. All you have to do is dodge every obstacle for 60 seconds. Definitely sounds easier than it seems, because those 60 seconds will be the longest in your ENTIRE LIFE. My favourite level has to be Hexagonestest. It's really challenging, but not overly frustrating like it's predecessor, Hexagones♥♥♥♥♥♥♥-the last level. It's also very nice in the contrast of color, making it nice to actually see the friggin' triangle.I used to play the Impossible Game on the PS3, and lemme tell you-this is much harder. It will throw attacks like you ain't ever seen before-sometimes going upwards to a 5-succession combo. What's even harder is how unlike the Impossible Game, the attacks are completely unpredictable. Yet, the hardest part is to keep at least %90 percent focused on the game. Why not %100? Well, if you're %100 focused, you're brain leaves reality, which-even in a game like this-is not good. You want to keep 90% focused on the game, while keeping %5 towards the keys you're using, and the other %5 towards reality. It's hard, but possible. Takes you maybe 500+ tries to complete Hexagones♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ (like I did), but it's SO worth it.Is it fun? Yes.Is it hard? F*CK YES.Is it worth buying for bragging rights? Oh, totally worth the $5.~I bought the expansion pack. ;PThis game for me receives a 12/10 for it's challenging levels, sheer frustration levels, and the level of ""OMFG"" after you've beaten the game. This is perfect for anyone looking for a real challenge of hand-eye coordination."
