,Recommended,221640,8237776,"Posted: 23 December, 2013",all,ARMmaster17,"Before I explain why this game is so addicting, let me explain the gameplay concept behind it:This is a war game. Every geometric shape with 3-6 verticies is out to get you. You play as one triangle, against the never ending waves of edges coming at you. Thousands of triangles will die because of your stupidity, slow reflexes, blindness, or any combination of those. After you play this, math class will be a nightmare, and hexagons will forever haunt you in your sleep.Now on to why this game is so fun:This games takes 1.52 seconds to learn, and all of eternity to master. After you play it the first time, you will keep playing for one of two reasons:1.You want to beat your new pathetic record2.You can't stand the fact that you still haven't beat your pathetic recordBuy this game only if you can accept defeat. If you can't, you should still buy it. This game will make hours seem like seconds. You will have fun. You will be confused. You will be angry. You will cuss. You will send your fist at your monitor. You will break the spacebar on your keyboard. you will cuss some more. You will scream with delight. You will repeat this cycle for all of eternity. Buy Super Hexagon now."
