,Recommended,221640,14531686,"Posted: 18 February, 2015",all,Generic,"Do I like Super Hexagon?TL;DR, yes I think it is an immensely satisfying game (for me!) and I heartily recommend it to everyone (hint: its £3, $5ish).Actual answerSuper Hexagon, as literally every review seems just aching to point out, is a minimalistic, epilepsy-inducing, stupendously difficult game, about... actually, make up your own plot: the triangle has been discovered by the infidel hexagons, and he has to escape from their shape-changing fortress by dodging parts of hexagons in a never ending battle of determination, geometry, and almost-2D-gaming. Or whatever.In order to survive, you will need the reflexes of a cat; the predictions of a cat; the many lives of a cat; the-- actually, just be a cat to win. Now that I have finished the introduction to this, the subliminal messages to worship all of cat kind have finally seeped into your puny human heads, and the reign of the Kitten Of Sauron can commence!All joking aside, this game is not everyone's cup of tea, and if you are the sort of person who gets frustrated and rage quits easily: LEAVE AND DO NOT EVER RETURN TO THIS GAME. If you are the sort who are determined to complete any game you start: prepare to have your will tested, your emotions subtly controlled, and your brain slowing turn to mulch as you become obsessed with hexagons and pentagons, as well as being constantly annoyed that Terry did not use base 10 for fractions of seconds. Think about your choice carefully, as I can only ramble for so long and there is time to kill. The fate of the Earth is in your hands, and only the true heroes will choose the correct choice, but only the people who choose wrong will understand which decision was right.I make no sense. Roll with it. It's been great getting hated on, spat at, and generally repressed by you internet ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥s who think an ant has no right to make reviews that barely make sense.Also, prepare for some not-so-natural progression in terms of levels. I completed: Hexagon, after 2 hours; Hexagoner,  after 3 hours; Hyper Hexagoner, after 15 hours; Hyper Hexagon, after 16 hours; Hexagonest, ???; Hyper Hexagonest, ???15/1 ~ GMA"
