,Recommended,221640,19588188,"Posted: 9 December, 2015",all,Intersection,"Do you have three dollars? Buy Super Hexagon, then. Looking by my mere three-hour playtime, it may not seem like the game is worth it, but that's because this game is very much reminiscent of old vector graphics coin-op games like Asteroids and Missile Command. Gameplay is simple: move left and right, dodge the walls. The art is appealing, the gameplay is ridiculously easy to learn but very grueling to master, the music is fantastic, and it's a game you can easily pick up and play at literally any time for just a few seconds at a time or for an hour or two if you feel up to the challenge. If you like arcade-style games or twitch reflex games, this is definitely a game worth getting."
