,Recommended,221640,7795292,"Posted: 27 November, 2013",all,El Flamenco Diablo,"You think at first, ""oh, this looks really simple, I could probably beat it in one hour,"" but then you would be wrong, dead wrong. The entire goal (if you can't tell by the video) is to guide your little triangle through an ever shifting pattern of walls, and survive for sixty seconds. It took over three hours for me to beat the first level, and it's so addicting, that it only felt like half an hour. Think you can do better? Try it. Think you'll get tired of it? Think again! The feminine computer's voice of ""game over"" every time you die is like one big taunt, mocking you, but at the same time, telling you to go on. There's no tutorial, and the difficulty for the first level is ""Hard"". If you're looking for a challenging, and incredibly addicting game, think about adding this little gem to your collection. Trust me, you'll thank me later."
