76561198016880157,Recommended,221640,7807978,"Posted: 28 November, 2013",all,Riik,"Gameplay: 8/10Simple yet fun. Super Hexagon offers an enjoyable yet simplistic classic experience. You probably look at the screenshots and trailers and think it's boring, but it's like tetris or bejeweled; once you start, you get addicted, only there's more, because each level is only a minute long, yet take a good while to complete on account of difficulty. Much more than say yawning your way through the early levels of tetris, or going from ""this is easy"" to ""aaaaaah!"".Visuals: 4/10The graphics to this game are simple, yet get the job done.  The lighting is somewhat psychodelic and trippy at first, but extended plays can result in headaches or migraines.Sound: 9/10Great classic synthetic music that makes me desperately want whatever synthesiser they used. The announcer lady doesn't get annoying, which is another plus, and the sound effects are functional. I'd give it a 10 if there was any ground breaking aspect to the sound, but there's not.Learning Curve: 9/10The easiest difficulty is hard. Yet the game doesn't require any explaining to play, beyond maybe a paragraph. It's quick to learn but not so to master. That is what a good learning curve is. The only reason it's not a 10 is because the easiest difficulty is 'hard', where maybe there should be a 'normal' as well.Replayability: 8/10This game isn't sandbox, so it won't keep bringing you back in a few years time to try something new. But the game is fun and score-based, so there's reason to play beyond completion. Plus the gameplay is just fun to just go on to simply play rather than to reach some sort of goal.Interface: 9/10The game is open to many kinds of inputs, and given its simplicity, these are never complicated. The controls are easy, but controlling the triangle can get frustrating at times when you overshoot or undershoot where you're trying to go. The UI is simple and easy to follow.Story: N/AThe game has no story. It is an arcade-style game.Support: N/AThe game has very very little room for bugs, works on simple OpenGL graphics, and is unlikely to get updates. Thus there's no real need for any support.Optimisation: N/AThe game's simple design means it can run on practically anything, so optimised graphics etc isn't an issue.Value for money: 10/10I just bought the game for under 40p. It's cheap even when not on sale, too.-----Overall:-----8.1 /10-----"
