,Recommended,221640,8077520,"Posted: 17 December, 2013",all,Jay,"A game that will test your sanity, as ""Game Over"" continues to echo throughout your room. Super Hexagon is a difficult, yet amazingly simple game that will keep you coming back as you see your time on each level go up. Progression is the key to this game, and if you are able to keep up with it's fast pace gameplay, you'll find yourself deeply enticed by the games colorful graphics and catchy music.You begin as a triangle outside of a hexagon and soon walls will close into that hexagon. Your goal is to naviagate around these walls, looking for that open space as to not be crushed by them. The idea is very simple, yet the gameplay is dependent on your ability to quickly move around these walls. You WILL hear ""Game Over"" a lot and it WILL be frustrating. But like I said before, progression is the key to this game and soon you will find yourself getting better at manuevering.There are 6 levels in total, 3 of which are unlocked by beating the beginning stages. Each stage has different patterns, with how the walls will move in on you. The colors, speed and music is also dependent on which stage you play. Each stage increases in difficulty and the speed ramps up significantly. So it's advise to start at the first stage and move your way up."
