,Recommended,221640,14568546,"Posted: 20 February, 2015",all,ImBoredToo,"Must own, especially since it occasionally goes on sale for like 29 cents. Very challenging and fun with an amazing soundtrack. My only criticism is the difficulty curve is kinda wonky. You may want to skip around after finishing 1 and 2.This game can technically be beaten in about 6 minutes, but it took me 34 hours. I initially avoided this because of my temper, but it really didn't get to me too often because every failure always feels like your fault. There's always a way through, and it takes 1 second to restart. If you eventually do get frustrated, the game takes almost no time to close or boot up. I recomend playing with vsync off, and not in fullscreen so you don't use your peripheral vision as much. Also this game will take a while to train your brain and hand eye coordination, so don't expect to beat it on the first day."
